					<head>Esther scroll</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79053644" rend="visible">
						<summary>The Book of Esther. </summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="1v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Megilat Ester </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">מגלת אסתר</title>
							<note>
								<p>Some reading differ from the masoretic כתיב. </p>
								<p>The Megillah is preceded by two benedictions. </p>
							</note>
							<decoNote type="border">Full borders around columns, inhabited with floral decorations, in watercolours.  <locus from="1r" to="1v"/>
							</decoNote>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment scroll of the 17th century. </p>
						<objectDesc form="scroll ">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment. </support>
								<extent>3 membranes, 17 columns. <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>114/140/240</height>
										<width>1850</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<collation>
									<p>3 membranes, with wooden roller and wooden case (+ short paper strip for attachment to roller). </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>The wooden case has minor losses to handle and ends.
</p>
									<p>The outermost membrane has non-sewn joint at centre, silked on recto to contain pigments.
</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="17" ruledLines="15 21" writtenLines="15 21">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Ruling by hard point,
membrane by membrane.</p>
									<p>Visible pricking. </p>
									<p>No tagin on שעטנזגץ, and one on the letter ח of חור, 1:6. </p>
									<p>The names of the sons of Haman arranged in 11 lines, in accordance with the rule. </p>
									<p>Sections 3:8 and 4:1 are open. </p>
									<p>Wooden roller and case (on new core: 140mm long, old case: 240mm long). </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Ashkenazi square script of the 17th century. First seven columns due to a later hand. </summary>
